# Initial UI Layout & Tailwind CSS Setup

This plan details the steps to configure Tailwind CSS within the existing Vite + React project and build the initial Dark Mode SPA layout as requested.

## Proposed Changes

We will execute this plan in two stages: Tooling Configuration and UI Component Development.

### Tooling Configuration

- **Install Dependencies**: `tailwindcss`, `postcss`, `autoprefixer` via npm.
- **Initialize Tailwind**: Create `tailwind.config.js` and `postcss.config.js` using `npx tailwindcss init -p`.
- **Configure Tailwind**:
  - Update `tailwind.config.js` content paths to include all React components.
  - Set up Dark Mode preferences and custom color tokens (e.g., deep dark backgrounds resembling Photoshop).
- **Global Styles**: Include Tailwind directives in `src/index.css` and configure global background and text colors to enforce the dark theme.
- **Icon Library**: Install `lucide-react` to use clean, modern SVGs for the requested icons (Upload, Grayscale, etc.).

### UI Component Development

We will divide the layout into a clean and componentized structure inside `src/`.

#### Component Structure

- **`src/components/layout/MainLayout.tsx`**: The main orchestrator connecting the three main sections.
- **`src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx`**: Left Panel. Contains vertical icon buttons for tools: `Upload`, `Grayscale`, `Low Pass (Blur)`, `High Pass (Sharpen)`, `Threshold`.
- **`src/components/workspace/CanvasArea.tsx`**: Central Area. Will feature two main placeholders side by side: Original Image and Processed Image.
- **`src/components/layout/Inspector.tsx`**: Right Panel. Will contain sliders/controls for currently selected tool properties (e.g., Intensity, Threshold level).
- **`src/App.tsx`**: Update to wrap everything inside the `MainLayout`.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> Please confirm if adding `lucide-react` for SVG icons is acceptable! It is highly recommended to have clean, customizable icons for the sidebar tools.
> 
> Also, confirm if you would like me to use any specific brand color or if a neutral dark theme (Slate/Zinc) resembling standard professional software like Photoshop is preferred.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Manual Verification
- I will run `npm run dev` and spawn a browser subagent to render the layout and verify if everything fits the screen perfectly without unexpected scrollbars (true SPA experience) and adheres to the dark mode requirements.
